Description: Handle sliver of Rhodian pottery transport amphora at neck join. Clay near fine pink-buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp with caduceus symbol.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 101a, 42. Name Sosikles. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, CEALEX BI 1151.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1049)
